---
layout: layouts/base.njk
order: 3
title: Pricing & Engagement
description: How sysf.io engagements work — a land-and-expand path from a fixed-scope Pilot to Production to a fully Air-gapped, on-prem rollout. Every tier is sovereign; pricing is scoped per engagement. Book a call to get a proposal.
extraSchema:
  "@context": "https://schema.org"
  "@type": "Service"
  serviceType: "Custom sovereign AI model development and productization"
  provider:
    "@type": "Organization"
    name: "sysf.io"
    url: "https://sysf.io"
  areaServed: ["CH", "EU"]
  description: "Custom fine-tuned AI models built on Apertus with retrieval, agents and guardrails, deployed in Swiss/EU jurisdiction or on-premise. Engagements range from a fixed-scope Pilot to Production to a fully air-gapped on-prem rollout."
  offers:
    "@type": "Offer"
    priceSpecification:
      "@type": "PriceSpecification"
      priceCurrency: "CHF"
    availability: "https://schema.org/InStock"
    description: "Pricing is scoped per engagement. Contact sysf.io for a proposal."
faq:
  - q: Why don't you list fixed prices?
    a: Every engagement differs in data, use cases, deployment target and compliance scope, so we price per engagement after a short scoping conversation. You get a clear, fixed-scope proposal before any commitment — no open-ended time-and-materials.
  - q: What does a Pilot typically involve?
    a: "A fixed-scope engagement on a single high-value use case — private data preparation, fine-tuning on Apertus, an evaluation report against agreed metrics (including a fine-tune vs. retrieval ablation), and a production roadmap. It's designed to prove value on your own data and de-risk the decision to go to production."
  - q: What happens to our data in a Pilot?
    a: If the Pilot runs in your environment, nothing ever leaves it. If you opt for our dedicated single-tenant Swiss cloud environment, your data is processed under a data-processing agreement and, at project end, all data and derived weights are deleted or handed over to you — your choice at scoping. Production and Air-gapped systems always run inside your own environment.
  - q: Is there an ongoing cost after we deploy?
    a: Production systems include an ongoing platform and support component — hosting or on-prem support, monitoring, evaluation and a maintenance cadence under a support agreement. We scope this transparently as part of the Production or Air-gapped proposal.
  - q: Do we own the model?
    a: Yes. Because we build on the open Apertus model and fine-tune on your data inside your environment, you retain ownership and control of the resulting model and can run it independently. A documented handover is a deliverable in every engagement — your exit strategy is part of the scope.
---
{% from "partials/components.njk" import sectionHead, faqList, cta %}

<section class="border-b border-ink-900/10 dark:border-white/10">
  <div class="container-x py-16 md:py-24">
    <p class="eyebrow">Pricing &amp; engagement</p>
    <h1 class="mt-4 max-w-4xl text-4xl font-bold leading-[1.08] tracking-tightest text-ink-900 md:text-5xl dark:text-white">
      Start small. Prove value. Scale to air-gapped.
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-6 max-w-2xl text-lg prose-muted md:text-xl">
      Every tier is sovereign — your data stays in your jurisdiction. Tiers differ in deployment depth, not in principle. Pricing is scoped per engagement — you get a fixed-scope proposal before any commitment.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Stages -->
<section class="container-x py-20 md:py-24">
  <div class="grid gap-5 md:grid-cols-3">
    {% set stages = [
      {
        t:"Pilot",
        for:"Prove value on one use case",
        d:"A fixed-scope engagement to validate sovereign AI on your own data.",
        price:"Fixed scope",
        pnote:"Priced after a 30-minute scoping call — no open-ended time-and-materials.",
        inc:[
          "One high-value use case",
          "Private, in-jurisdiction data prep",
          "Fine-tuning & retrieval on Apertus",
          "Evaluation report vs. agreed metrics",
          "Production roadmap",
          "Your environment or dedicated Swiss cloud"
        ]
      },
      {
        t:"Production",
        for:"The pilot, hardened for daily use",
        featured:true,
        d:"Take the proven use case to a maintained production system.",
        price:"Fixed build + support",
        pnote:"Build priced per scope; support & maintenance as a transparent ongoing component.",
        inc:[
          "Everything in Pilot",
          "Agents, RAG & tools wired to your systems",
          "Safety & PII guardrails",
          "Swiss cloud or on-prem deployment",
          "Monitoring & evaluation",
          "Support & maintenance agreement"
        ]
      },
      {
        t:"Air-gapped",
        for:"Regulated / most sensitive environments",
        d:"A fully isolated rollout for environments where nothing crosses the wire.",
        price:"Individually scoped",
        pnote:"Scoped with your infrastructure and compliance teams.",
        inc:[
          "Everything in Production",
          "Fully on-prem / confidential compute",
          "Multiple models & agents",
          "Dedicated operations",
          "Compliance & audit documentation",
          "Enterprise support commitments"
        ]
      }
    ] %}
    {% for s in stages %}
    <div class="relative rounded-lg border border-neutral-200 bg-white p-8 shadow-sm dark:border-white/10 dark:bg-ink-950 {{ 'ring-2 ring-red-500 ring-inset shadow-md' if s.featured }}">
      {% if s.featured %}<div class="absolute right-6 top-6 rounded-full bg-red-600 px-2.5 py-1 text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.12em] text-white">Most common</div>{% endif %}
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold tracking-tightest text-ink-900 dark:text-white">{{ s.t }}</h2>
      <p class="mt-1 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-swiss">{{ s.for }}</p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-sm prose-muted">{{ s.d }}</p>
      <div class="mt-6 border-t border-ink-900/10 pt-6 dark:border-white/10">
        <div class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tightest text-ink-900 dark:text-white">{{ s.price }}</div>
        <p class="mt-1 text-xs text-ink-500">{{ s.pnote }}</p>
      </div>
      <ul class="mt-6 space-y-2.5">
        {% for i in s.inc %}
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2.5 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-ink-300">
          <svg class="mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 shrink-0 text-swiss" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.7 5.3a1 1 0 0 1 0 1.4l-7.5 7.5a1 1 0 0 1-1.4 0L3.3 10.7a1 1 0 1 1 1.4-1.4l3.1 3.1 6.8-6.8a1 1 0 0 1 1.4 0Z" clip-rule="evenodd"/></svg>
          {{ i }}
        </li>
        {% endfor %}
      </ul>
      <a href="/contact/" class="mt-8 w-full {{ 'btn-primary' if s.featured else 'btn-ghost' }}">Book a call</a>
    </div>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>

  <p class="mt-6 text-sm prose-muted">The Pilot's central deliverable is the evaluation report. <a class="link-underline" href="/reports/finma-ablation/">See an example</a> — a reproducible four-way ablation of Apertus-8B on Swiss FINMA circular Q&amp;A.</p>

  <div class="mt-8 flex flex-col gap-4 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm dark:border-white/10 dark:bg-ink-950 sm:flex-row sm:items-center sm:justify-between md:p-8">
    <div>
      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold tracking-tightest text-ink-900 dark:text-white">Not sure which tier fits?</h2>
      <p class="mt-1 text-sm prose-muted">Spend two minutes in the build configurator — pick your model, data handling and deployment, and it suggests a tier and hands you a one-page spec to send us.</p>
    </div>
    <a href="/configure/" class="btn-primary shrink-0">Configure your build →</a>
  </div>

  <!-- Add-ons -->
  <div class="mt-10 border border-ink-900/10 p-6 dark:border-white/10">
    <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-x-6 gap-y-2 text-sm">
      <span class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-ink-500">Add-ons</span>
      {% for a in ["Compliance & audit pack", "Additional languages", "Additional use cases", "Managed hosting"] %}
      <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 font-medium text-ink-700 dark:text-ink-300"><span class="h-1.5 w-1.5 bg-swiss"></span>{{ a }}</span>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
    <p class="mt-4 text-xs text-ink-500">The compliance &amp; audit pack includes: model card, training-data lineage record, data-processing agreement template, technical &amp; organisational measures (TOMs), EU AI Act risk-classification worksheet, and the evaluation report.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="border-t border-ink-900/10 py-20 dark:border-white/10 md:py-28">
  <div class="container-x grid gap-12 md:grid-cols-12">
    <div class="md:col-span-4">{{ sectionHead("FAQ", "Pricing questions.") }}</div>
    <div class="md:col-span-7 md:col-start-6">{{ faqList(faq) }}</div>
  </div>
</section>

{{ cta("Let's scope your engagement.", "A short call is enough to shape a fixed-scope proposal for your first use case.") }}
